# README Updates

- When making meaningful implementation, navigation, route, service, content-structure, or developer workflow changes, check whether `README.md` should be updated in the same change.
- Update `README.md` when behavior, available pages, routes, commands, setup steps, dependencies, or project conventions change.
- For service/navigation changes, document new or changed service pages and any important menu structure so future contributors can understand the site map.
- Keep README edits concise and scoped to the change. Do not rewrite unrelated sections unless the user asks.
